comments.content:
@paragraph: It took me a minute, but lol.

Regrettably this conversation took place this afternoon, between myself and one of my the owners. I was putting together some options for a designer product lookbook, so it was basically only a headline and a tagline for each page. It could have been worse, of course. I managed to put together a couple of other options before I left, I was just so frustrated that I had to get it out before I could even see straight.

@sii: I have to go with James here. After all of the folks I have seen laid off lately, I am glad to have _any_ job, even if it is run by idiots.

Funny, I thought moving here (NYC) from FL was a good career move.

@James: I am definitely going to put more things together in my downtime. On my own comp, of course.

@DanGayle

No!

No matter how much you ridicule it I will continue to believe that a nice, breezy drop shadow can be OKAY for some jobs.

@all, you guys crack me up.

It is all so true, and I know I just need to toughen up. I feel like i try so hard to grow, to be better, and at the end of the day, it's really not up to me. I guess that's the hardest part (as stated by Dr. J), and I just need to know when to deal with it.

I'm taking some time (now that the economy is slow) to build my portfolio. When people are spending money again, I plan on being ready to go it alone.

Again, thank you. Sometimes, it is easy to feel like I am the only one who deals with this bs.

@James, I agree with what Ricardo said.

Time to go fill in some more white space ;-)
